William Beimers

Bio

William Beimers studies plasma proteomics technologies and their applications for systems biology as a PhD student in the Coon Lab at UW-Madison. He is interested in the incorporation of large multi-omics datasets using powerful bioinformatics tools. Outside of work he is an avid rock climber and amateur horn player.

Experience

University of Wisconsin, Madison | Madison, WI
Ph.D.in Biochemistry | September 2022 - Present

Mayo Clinic Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology | Rochester, MN
Graduate Research Education Program | June 2020 - July 2022

St.Olaf College | Northfield, MN
B.A. in Chemistry and Music | September 2016 - May 2020
